// Development seed contract
// Files: package.json, scripts/seed-dev.ts, supabase/seed.sql, docs/DEVELOPMENT.md, .env.example

// npm script
// - `npm run seed:dev` => `node --experimental-strip-types scripts/seed-dev.ts`

// Required server-side env
// - SUPABASE_URL
// - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
// Both are documented in .env.example and docs/DEVELOPMENT.md.

// scripts/seed-dev.ts behavior
// - Creates or reuses auth users `dev.alice@worktracker.local` and `dev.bob@worktracker.local`
// - Upserts matching public.users profile rows
// - Upserts removable sample `time_entries` and overall `monthly_goals` using fixed row IDs for idempotency
// - Supports flags: `--dry-run`, `--skip-users`, `--skip-samples`
// - Never seeds categories

// supabase/seed.sql behavior
// - Local SQL fallback only
// - Does NOT create auth users
// - Upserts the same removable sample `time_entries` and `monthly_goals` for the two dev emails if those users already exist
// - Never seeds categories

// Seed markers
// - Sample time entry notes are prefixed with `[Seed - removable]` so they can be safely deleted after testing.
